if (<boolean-expression>) 
	<statement>
else if (<boolean-expression>) {
	<statement>
	<statement>
} else 
	<statement>
	
// "dangling else" in case we don't use curling brackets
// else always refers to the latest if operator


- ternary operator ("τριαδικός χειριστής")
  ----------------
 <boolean-expression> ? <value A> : <value B>

if (<boolean-expression>) 
	<value A>
else 
	<value B>

<b> ? <Class A> : <Class a> => Class A
<b> ? <Class A> : <Class B> => Most specific supertype to which
							   both Class A and B are assignable